It’s easy to measure progress in lines of code, or in user counts, or in funding rounds. But the real work — the kind that defines what we’re building — happens in the quiet moments. The ones where you’re not chasing metrics, but chasing clarity. At Diedai, we’re not just solving for today’s problems — we’re solving for the day when the system doesn’t just work, but feels like it was built